    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN149.2-kilavi">talaimakaṉ ṟaṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to his heart.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN149.2">
              <l>ciṟupuṉ citalai cēṇmuyaṉ ṟeṭutta</l>
              <l>neṭuñcem puṟṟat toṭuṅkirai muṇaiyiṟ</l>
              <l>pullarai <supplied>yi</supplied>ruppait toḷḷai vāṉpūp</l>
              <l>peruṅkai yeṇki ṉiruṅkiḷaik kavaru</l>
              <l>matta nīḷiṭaip pōki naṉṟu</l>
              <l>maritucey viḻupporu ḷeḷitiṉiṟ peṟiṉum</l>
              <l>vārēṉ vāḻiye ṉeñcē cēralar</l>
              <l>cuḷḷiyam pēryāṟṟu veṇṇurai kalaṅka</l>
              <l>yavaṉar tanta viṉaimā ṇaṉkalam</l>
              <l>poṉṉoṭu vantu kaṟiyoṭu peyarum</l>
              <l>vaḷaṅkeḻu muciṟi yārppeḻa vaḷaii</l>
              <l>yaruñcamaṅ kaṭantu paṭivam vauviya</l>
              <l>neṭunal yāṉai yaṭupōrc ceḻiyaṉ</l>
              <l>koṭinuṭaṅku maṟukiṟ kūṭaṟ kuṭātu</l>
              <l>palpoṟi maññai velkoṭi yuyariya</l>
              <l>voṭiyā viḻavi ṉeṭiyōṉ kuṉṟattu</l>
              <l>vaṇṭupaṭa nīṭiya kuṇṭucuṉai nīlat</l>
              <l>tetirmalarp piṇaiya laṉṉaviva</l>
              <l>ḷarimatar maḻaikkaṇ ṭeṇpaṉi koḷavē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Even if, going the long way on the road, (5a-c)</l>
                <l>where, when disliking the prey contained in the tall red ant hill (2)</l>
                <l>raised with effort [visible from] the distance by the little, lowly ants, (1)</l>
                <l>the dark relatives of the large-pawed anteater seize (4)</l>
                <l>the tubular white flowers of the low-trunked Mahua tree, (3)</l>
                <l>[I] were to obtain easily the excellent wealth very difficult to make, (5d-6)</l>
                <l>I would not come, my heart, (7a-c)</l>
                <l>– so that the red-streaked proud rain eyes would hold clear dew (19)</l>
                <l>of her who is like a wreath of contrasting blossoms (18)</l>
                <l>of blue lotus from the deep pool, elongated so that bees settle [there], (17)</l>
                <l>on the hill of the Tall one in unbroken festivals (16)</l>
                <l>when the many-dotted peacock is raised as a victory banner, (15)</l>
                <l>to the west of Kūṭal, with streets where flags sway, (14)</l>
                <l>of Ceḻiyaṉ, of deadly battle, with large good elephants (13)</l>
                <l>who snatched the image after besieging, so that a tumult arose,</l>
                <l>fertile Muciṟi, overcoming it in a difficult battle, (11f.)</l>
                <l rend="indent8">[the city] of the Cēra, (7d)</l>
                <l>where the good vessels of glorious workmanship that were brought by the Yavaṉar (9)</l>
                <l>come with gold [and] return with pepper, (10)</l>
                <l>so that white foam is stirred up in the big Cuḷḷi river. (8)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
